  "body": " /kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen using emptyDir with hugepages medium:\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: Pod\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: example\r\nspec:\r\n  containers:\r\n  - image: ubuntu\r\n    command:\r\n    - sleep\r\n    - inf\r\n    name: example\r\n    volumeMounts:\r\n    - mountPath: /hugepages\r\n      name: hugepage\r\n    resources:\r\n      requests:\r\n        hugepages-2Mi: 100Mi\r\n      limits:\r\n        hugepages-2Mi: 100Mi\r\n  volumes:\r\n  - name: hugepage\r\n    emptyDir:\r\n      medium: HugePages\r\n```\r\n\r\nI got following error in dmesg:\r\n```\r\nhugetlbfs: Bad mount option: \"pageSize=2Mi\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nI expected Kubernetes to mount a hugetlbfs backed volume inside pod.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nRun above manifest `kube-apiserver` has to be launched with `--feature-gates=\"HugePages=true\"` and k8s node has to have available at least 50 pages of size 2Mi.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nIt is caused because there is a typo instead of `pageSize` it should be `pagesize`.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): `v1.9.0-alpha.0.525+99b2ee16977b45-dirty`\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**:  `OpenStack`\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n```\r\nNAME=\"Ubuntu\"\r\nVERSION=\"16.04.1 LTS (Xenial Xerus)\"\r\nID=ubuntu\r\nID_LIKE=debian\r\nPRETTY_NAME=\"Ubuntu 16.04.1 LTS\"\r\nVERSION_ID=\"16.04\"\r\nHOME_URL=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/\"\r\nSUPPORT_URL=\"http://help.ubuntu.com/\"\r\nBUG_REPORT_URL=\"http://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/\"\r\nVERSION_CODENAME=xenial\r\nUBUNTU_CODENAME=xenial\r\n```\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): `Linux hugepages 4.4.0-57-generic`",
